# Project overview

This project is a Java 21 Spring Boot command-line Kafka producer test tool.

Use YAML configuration files as the primary user interface.

Spring profiles are for environment-level defaults. External run files are for test scenarios.

Do not implement consumer or Kafka Streams functionality unless explicitly requested.

Use package-by-feature organization:

- cli
- config
- kafka
- payload
- execution
- statistics
- util

Keep workload generation, Kafka sending, and statistics output separated so CSV I/O cannot distort producer callbacks.
